This paper deals with the Nakamura number of simple games, which is a concept in computational game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the properties of simple games, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The study of preference aggregation and ranking is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
